<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-06-26T15:28:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-06-26T15:28:00-05:00" n="713" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d713">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">690D.91/6–2552: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Embassy in
                                        Pakistan</gloss></hi><note n="1" xml:id="d713fn1">This
                                    telegram was repeated for information to New York.</note></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">secret<lb/>priority</hi></seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-06-26T16:28:00-04:00">June 26, 1952—4:28
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1396. Re Kashmir. <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss>’s <gloss target="#t_niact1">niact</gloss> tel 1563.<note n="2" xml:id="d713fn2"><ref target="#d712"><hi rend="italic">Supra</hi></ref>.</note></p>
                            <p>In view: (a) indicated intention of <gloss target="#t_Pak1">Pak</gloss> Del in NY to stop negots with <persName corresp="#p_GDF1">Graham</persName> on June 26 or shortly
                                thereafter; (b) info contained in <gloss target="#t_reftel1">reftel</gloss> indicating poss willingness <persName corresp="#p_NK1">Nazimuddin</persName> to consider different
                                figure on troop quantum; (c) our understanding <persName corresp="#p_GDF1">Graham</persName> desires <persName corresp="#p_KGMA1">Ayub</persName> stay in NY, you are requested
                                urge <persName corresp="#p_NK1">Nazimuddin</persName> or <persName corresp="#p_KCSM1">Zafrulla</persName> as you see fit to direct
                                    <persName corresp="#p_KGMA1">Ayub</persName> to remain in NY for
                                poss further negots along lines <persName corresp="#p_NK1">Nazimuddin</persName> has indicated <gloss target="#t_GOP1">GOP</gloss> might be prepared to consider. You may indicates US
                                greatly interested in <persName corresp="#p_NK1">Nazimuddin</persName>’s consideration of new figure for troop
                                quantum.</p>
                            <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_BDKE1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Bruce</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>